Theoretical Problems 

Problem 1.1

Bayes Rule: 

h(x) = sigma(x) == sigma';

X1: 0 1 1 0
X2: 2 3 3 2
X3: 0 1 1 0
X4: 2 3 3 2
X5: 0 1 1 0
X6: 2 3 3 2
X7: 0 1 1 0
X8: 2 3 3 2
X9: 0 1 1 0

H = { h = sigma(x) == sgm : smg belongs to R }

uml = 1 / sum(k=1 .. n) |xi| sum(i=1 .. n) 1/len(xi) sum(i=1 .. len(xi))xij
o^2ml = 1/n sum(i = 1 .. n) ( 1 / len(xi) sum(j = 1 .. len(xi)) ( xij - uml))^2)
oml = sqrt(o^2ml)
